Egypt â€™s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
dropped for the first time in four days, slipping less than 0.1
percent to 4,727.4 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Orascom Development Holding AG (ODHN)   jumped 9.3
percent, the most since Bloomberg started tracking the shares in
December 2009, to 6.97 Egyptian pounds. The Altdorf,
Switzerland-based resorts developer said its Egyptian subsidiary
Orascom Hotels & Development has reached a full settlement with
the Egyptian Financial Supervisory Authority, nullifying the
two-year jail sentence and fine against its chairman Samih Sawiris.  Six of October Development & Investment (OCDI)  Co
retreated the most in almost two weeks, losing 1.2 percent to
17.08 pounds. The Cairo-based luxury-real estate developer known
as Sodic reported a first-half loss of 120 million pounds ($20
million) after a profit of 50.7 million pounds in the year-
earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
